此站位於地面以下120英呎，設有4部升降機以及位於車站北端連接兩個[[側式月台|側式月台]]的一條行人天橋。車站於1096年5月30日啟用時<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://query.nytimes.com/mem/archive-free/pdf?res=9F00E3D9143DE733A25753C3A9639C946797D6CF|title=Express to 221st Street: Will Run In the Subway To-day–New 181st Street Station Ready.|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=September 1, 2016|archive-date=2016-09-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160914101444/http://query.nytimes.com/mem/archive-free/pdf?res=9F00E3D9143DE733A25753C3A9639C946797D6CF|dead-url=no}}</ref>，只有車站東側設有兩部升降機，但1909年西側亦加入了兩部升降機<ref>{{cite web | title=The New York Times: Friday April 23, 1909 | website=NYTimes.com | date=1909-04-23 | url=http://timesmachine.nytimes.com/timesmachine/1909/04/23/101737198.html | accessdate=2016-07-16}}</ref>。車站南端有證據證明曾有兩條已關閉的行人天橋和人手控制的{{link-en|雙層升降機|double-deck elevator}}<ref>{{cite web | last=Pirmann | first=David | last2=Darlington | first2=Peggy | title=IRT West Side Line: 181st Street | website=www.nycsubway.org | url=http://www.nycsubway.org/wiki/IRT_West_Side_Line#181st_Street | accessdate=2016-07-16 | archive-date=2017-01-06 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170106212734/http://www.nycsubway.org/wiki/IRT_West_Side_Line#181st_Street | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

車站只有一條緊急樓梯，因此所有乘客除緊急情況下必需使用升降機進出車站。車站服務[[葉史瓦大學|葉史瓦大學]]和[[喬治·華盛頓大橋|喬治·華盛頓大橋]]。

==天花板倒塌==
2009年8月16日約晚上10時30分，位於車站頂部一段25英呎長的磚於35英呎高的天花板倒塌，散佈於上下行的軌道和月台，無人受傷<ref name="Dwyer 2009">{{cite web | last=Dwyer | first=Jim | title=Subway Station Ceilings Were Built to Last, but Not Forever | website=The New York Times | date=August 18, 2009 | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/08/19/nyregion/19about.html | accessdate=July 16, 2016 | archive-date=2020-07-22 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200722193106/https://www.nytimes.com/2009/08/19/nyregion/19about.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>。這導致168街車站及迪克曼街車站來回方向的1號線列車服務必需暫停8天。該段期間，[[大都會運輸署|大都會運輸署]]提供免費接駁巴士來往168街和迪克曼街<ref>{{cite news |title=Subway station repairs to take days |url=http://abclocal.go.com/wabc/story?section=resources/traffic&id=6969234 |publisher=''[[WABC-TV|WABC-TV]] news'' |date=2009-08-18 |accessdate=2009-08-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110604043702/http://abclocal.go.com/wabc/story?section=resources%2Ftraffic&id=6969234 |archive-date=2011-06-04 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref name=NYT0824>{{cite news |title=Service on No. 1 Subway Line Is Largely Restored |url=http://cityroom.blogs.nytimes.com/2009/08/24/service-on-no-1-subway-line-is-largely-restored/ |work=The New York Times |first=Michael M. |last=Grynbaum |date=2009-08-24 |accessdate=2009-08-24 |archive-date=2012-02-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120226004141/http://cityroom.blogs.nytimes.com/2009/08/24/service-on-no-1-subway-line-is-largely-restored/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。全線服務於2009年8月24日恢復，但仍然不停靠181街車站<ref name=NYT0824 />。車站於2009年8月31日重開<ref>{{cite news |title=No. 1 Line Service Restored to 181st Street |url=http://www.mta.info/mta/news/releases/?en=090830-NYCT130 |publisher=''[[大都會運輸署|大都會運輸署]]'' |date=2009-08-30 |accessdate=2009-08-31 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5jWKatLcC?url=http://www.mta.info/mta/news/releases/?en=090830-NYCT130 |archivedate=2009-09-03 |deadurl=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Subway Misery Has Express Stop At 181st Street |url=http://www.ny1.com/content/124760/subway-misery-has-express-stop-at-181st-street |work=[[NY1|NY1]] |accessdate=2010-09-01 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120226004146/http://www.ny1.com/content/124760/subway-misery-has-express-stop-at-181st-street |archivedate=2012-02-26 }}</ref>。

根據[[紐約市公共運輸局|紐約市公共運輸局]]主建築師Judith M. Kunoff，2007年同一車站亦曾有部份天花板倒塌<ref>{{cite news |title=Subway Station Ceilings Were Built to Last, but Not Forever |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2009/08/19/nyregion/19about.html |work=紐約時報 |first=Jim |last=Dwyer |date=2009-08-18 |accessdate=2009-08-24 |archive-date=2020-07-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200722193106/https://www.nytimes.com/2009/08/19/nyregion/19about.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

根據[[NY1|NY1]]，車站修緝花費3000萬美元，而且直至2012年末才開始動工<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.ny1.com/content/news_beats/transit/148777/washington-heights-straphangers-annoyed-at-long-delayed-subway-station-repairs| title=Washington Heights Straphangers Annoyed At Long-Delayed Subway Station Repairs| work=[[NY1|NY1]]| first=Tina| last=Redwine| date=2011-10-11| accessdate=2011-10-12| deadurl=yes| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120226004151/http://www.ny1.com/content/news_beats/transit/148777/washington-heights-straphangers-annoyed-at-long-delayed-subway-station-repairs| archivedate=2012-02-26}}</ref>。

